Rating: 3
My mom's pear treee was overloaded and so was my fig tree -- so I combined the two for this crumble with great results. Using the pears and figs, instead of raisins, I also used pecans instead of walnuts. I used a smaller, square pan and as a result didn't need all the topping. For whatever reason, it needed an additional 20-plus minutes to reach that brown and bubbling stage. We ate it with vanilla ice cream -- I could have devoured the whole pan in one sitting but made myself save some for later. I am making it again this week for my mom!

